<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-081-978  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 081 978.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  Feb 13 1989 n525 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Bush puts defense growth on hold.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Van Nostrand, Jim; Robinson, Brian.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>President Bush endorses a no-growth 1990 defense budget andproposes to upgrade the White House science advisor to theposition of presidential assistant for science and technology.andO;The Bush defense budget wipes out a $2.6 billion increase inPresident Reagan's proposed 1990 budget but will still be thefirst time in five years that the Pentagon budget has not beencut, providing Congress approves.andP;  Bush gave the Department ofDefense 60 days to develop a reduced budget that still maintainsmodernization programs for nuclear and non-nuclear weaponry andother ongoing military programs.andP;  He will continue to supportStrategic Defense Initiative (SDI) development.andP;  The new scienceand technology advisor will report directly to the president andwill be involved in high-level, inter-agency policy groups.andP;  Bushhas also endorsed other federal science and technologyinitiatives.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Goals and ObjectivesBudgetingMilitaryNational GovernmentProposalUnited States. Department of Defense.andO;Person:    Bush, George (economic policy).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>